venues.parkingDetail: A limited number of parking spaces are available along Mount Royal Avenue (including several handicapped accessible locations) and other nearby streets. Oliver Street.
venues.accessibleSeatingDetail: If you are in need of accessible seating please call (410) 900-1165 Accessible seating tickets will be held at Will Call and can be picked up 2 hours before the performance.

generalInfo.generalRule: ARRIVE EARLY All packages, including briefcases and pocketbooks, will be inspected prior to entry. Please be mindful of traffic conditions, as downtown Baltimore can be quite congested, especially during special events and the holiday season. All patrons will continue to go through a screening process upon entry. As delays are expected, The Lyric requests that for all events, ticket holders arrive as early as possible. Guests are strongly discouraged from bringing packages, briefcases, knapsacks and video equipment to the venue. No smoking permitted anywhere in The Lyric No recording devices permitted No outside food or drink permitted
generalInfo.childRule: A child under one year of age does not require a ticket, but will sit on the parent or guardians lap during the show. If a child has celebrated their first birthday, a ticket is required. Some shows are age restricted. Please refer to the venue website for more information.

boxOfficeInfo.openHoursDetail: Purchase tickets at the Murphy Fine Arts Center (MFAC) ticket office located at the front entrance (on the 2nd floor) of the MFAC located at 2201 Argonne Drive. boxOfficeInfo.willCallDetail: Will call tickets may be picked up beginning one hour prior to event at MFAC box office (located at the MFAC main entrance). Customers must present the credit card used to purchase the tickets as well as a photo ID.

venues.parkingDetail: Free, off-street parking is available in the parking lot marked Y-Lot. Access lot by turning right onto McCallum Dr. (on left side of MFAC). Travel up hill, pass the 'X' Parking Lot (PERMIT PARKING ONLY) on right. At end of 'X' Parking Lot, bear right at black fence. Look for 'Y' Parking Lot-which is the general parking lot for Murphy Fine Arts Center events. As you walk toward the building, enter the MFAC through bank of doors (in the that face the plaza)

generalInfo.generalRule: Late Seating: To ensure minimal disruption to our patrons once a performance has started, latecomers will be seated at the discretion and direction of the Front of House Manager during an appropriate break in the performance. There are no refunds or discounts for late arrivals. Please note that original seating cannot be guaranteed for latecomers.
generalInfo.childRule: Everyone--regardless of age--must have a ticket. Children (or anyone) causing distractions or disruptions (i.e. making sounds, crying, talking of any type) must exit the theatre. Please keep in mind that many performances and events are not appropriate for babies and young children.

events.name: Preakness Live - Infield Concert at the Preakness Stakes
events.info: This year Preakness LIVE will take over the Pimlico infield evolving the Infield Fest experience to usher in a new era for live music, entertainment, arts and culture on Preakness day. Celebrated singer, songwriter, producer and musician Bruno Mars, who has sold over 200 million singles worldwide, will return to the legendary Pimlico infield to bring his 24-karat magic back to Baltimore, 11-years after his first performance at the Preakness. Preakness LIVE will feature a full day of live music and entertainment beginning at 10:30 a.m. on Saturday, May 20 with performances by Grammy nominated musical duo SOFI TUKKER, DJ Chantel Jeffries, Martin 2 Smoove and many more.

events.info: All patrons regardless of age require a ticket. Hershey Theatre is a historic venue. There are no elevators to the Loge and Balcony sections. Artist(s) subject to change. Due to security enhancements, please arrive at least 45-60 minutes prior to event time. Please only bring essential items with you. The Hershey Theatre will only permit bags 5"x8"x1" or smaller, which includes hand clutches, wristlets and small purses. Any bags/backpacks that are larger in size will need to be returned to the owners vehicle or disposed of. Tickets can be purchased online until the event start time. After this time, if tickets are still available, they can be purchased at the Hershey Theatre Box office No Audio/Video Recording.

events.name: boygenius | Re:SET
events.pleaseNote: Re:SET is Rain or Shine, no refunds or exchanges. ACCESSIBLE SEATING: People requiring mobility accessible seating can purchase online through Ticketmaster or at the Merriweather box office amongst all ticket tiers. Buy as GA pavilion, GA lawn or VIP.. Upon arriving at the venue, let venue staff know you have an ADA need and you will be directed to your seating location. We have wheelchair- and scooter-accessible locations where patrons can remain in their wheelchairs or transfer to theater/concert seats. Note: Companion seats are plastic folding chairs. Wheelchair-accessible and companion seats are located throughout Section 100, in Row Z of Sections 200-204, and in Row JJ of Sections 300-302. Lawn ADA will be located in the pavilion behind Section 300.
